##Chun Yeung estate isolation diary 02 | March 8-march 10 the weather cleared

Micro signal

Features, life / Work / cat, and talk to you ~ 

Sunday, March 8,2020, day 4 of Quarantine

Wuhan confirmed 41 new cases yesterday, finally fell below 50.

On the first day of my stay in Jun Yang estate, I sent a friend circle, because the company team has held more than 20 online meetings every morning in February. They all said that 21 days can form a habit, i wonder if the 14 days of isolation will form a habit?

There's been a change in the body clock. Wake up at 8:30 a.m. Sharp to the Breakfast Bell, the regular 12:00 Lunch and 6:00 dinner.

At home in Wuhan, we always have a lunch between 1:00 and 4:00 in the afternoon, dinner around 8:00 in the evening, don't go to bed until 2:00 at night, and find many friends are still awake in the early morning.

Day In and day out, the date, the week, the time, and the number of days in lockdown, especially when there are 1,000 new cases a day, will certainly not be lifted tomorrow, nothing in particular is going to happen, and the epidemic is not going to get any worse than it is today.

Desperate. Jpg Is often used as an Emoji, a bittersweet joke.

In Junyang estate often feel hungry this is very strange, from the beginning to the isolation camp, do not know why always feel can eat something again, before in Wuhan home did not have such. I'm glad I'm not alone. I feel the same way when I have a camper.

Maybe it's because life is full. Morning meetings, after work, chatting with fellow campers and writing, taking videos, doing laundry (there are no washing machines in the camps, all clothes are hand-washed) , and online training and meetings, time flies.

The average daily screen time this week was 25% more than last week, according to the mobile phone, as people spent more time refreshing messages from wechat this week, such as whether they had received a notice from the Immigration Department, take photos and videos along the way to the back, edit videos, and exchange messages with fellow campers on Wechat after isolation, etc. .

The obvious downside is that it feels like the Myopia is getting worse.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
More screen use, eyes almost "blind" 

It's International Women's Day Day.

Sir, the film features a documentary about Xu Li, a 33-year-old mother in Wuhan who volunteered to deliver supplies to hospitals during the outbreak.

Before that, Fang Fang's Arrow through the heart and Chi Li's life show are classic works of Wuhan Women Writers Describing Wuhan Heroine.

"South Station Party" has not had time to go to the cinema to see, the new year film and even the Valentine's Day file film, also because of the epidemic reasons and put aside, pull file. Last year, there were many friends said the movie winter movie winter winter, did not expect "2019 is the last 10 years in the worst year, but the next 10 years the best year" a prophecy.

An aunt in Shanghai told me that I had never really met Wuhan people before, but this time I found that Wuhan people are strong, brave, and mutual help, and Wuhan people are very grateful.

Aunt's girl to fight the plague came to Wuhan, this month also infected with the temperament of Wuhan Women. "women are the main force in this battle, including the fiery sister-in-law of Wuhan. "

"Li Li Cha Huo" with "birds of a feather, birds of a Cui Hang" gentle version of the Han scolded justifiably punctured the group buying chaos; Castle peak residents in the windows downstairs shouted "are fake. ". It's too hard.

Strong and brave since needless to say, the epidemic raging Wuhan is such a sad and desolate hero of the city, gritting one's teeth to survive.

Talk of "gratitude" because, March 6 said to carry out "gratitude" education, attracted public anger. You can't be thankful for a giant wound that's not fully healed, not to mention the other way around.

There are so many absurdities in this epidemic that you have to get used to the idea of "abnormal operation. ".

For example, the production of face masks is 1.08 million, 1.8 billion, or 10.8 billion. For example, after the press conference, how did the people on the stage start clapping by themselves CCTV reporters from the battlefields and drug-kingpin dens can not get into the warehouses where the supplies are stored; why the supplies airdropped into the "black hole" of Wuhan from all over the world simply can not reach the hospitals most in need; He said he came in 98.6% of the time. Why is he the other 1.4% 

I used to say the Internet has no memory. Not this time, it won't. It is no use to delete the post, because all the things have been cut out of people's hearts.

Let's hope this outbreak can really change Wuhan and the whole country, even at such a great cost.

Would it have been better, or worse, if the new crown had originated not in Wuhan (it has not yet been found) but elsewhere?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
One piece of exciting good news today is the defending title of Zhang Weili UFC.

In an interview after the race, she said she had traveled extensively to compete in the United States because of the outbreak. (immigration restrictions allowed her to stop in Thailand and Dubai for 14 days each.) "I hope my country can get over the epidemic quickly, but now the epidemic is no longer a matter for the Chinese people, but for all mankind. I hope we can work together to overcome the epidemic. ". The video made my eyes water.

Friends Circle someone said, "Not Happy Goddess Festival, is the goddess of War Festival happy! " In the front of the nurses, but also the most beautiful female soldiers.

There is a new buzz in the WECHAT group of Junyang estate -- A "cannon" has been discovered on the opposite floor (telephoto) .

Huawei mobile phone users online sure enough to find the opposite corner of the top floor of the room, a window with a long lens mounted on the camera, the direction of the lower floor, the window there are two people in turn "watching. ". It's a cop show.

I'm a little confused. What do we have here? Taking pictures of people sitting around in their rooms, "pig's life" ? Or is there an ambulance coming in and out of the downstairs entrance?

After a discussion, a group of enthusiastic friends summoned the courage to call 999.

The police responded that unless there was evidence that he had taken it personally, there was no way to go upstairs and stop it from being a public social event or even a licensed "Paparazzi. ". "consider yourself a star. " Close the curtains if you don't mind.

Another new learning point is learning how to DIY the dryer in your room. A clever camper taught us to turn the heater on low heat, do not shake the head, put in the simple wardrobe, about 3-4 hours can be dried, and Taobao selling dryer principle. The campers are so cute

March 9,2020. Quarantine Day five

At 23:59 the night before, after posting the previous article, it was forwarded to a wechat group in Hubei Province.

There are still many people in Hubei waiting to return home to Hong Kong. Others have been stranded in Wuhan and given up their first trip back to Hong Kong because of concerns about life in the camps, such as the inconvenience of babies and toddlers. I hope that this record can also provide them with reference.

Did Not expect that many groups of friends have not slept at night, after reading the article expressed support.

"There's so much feeling in my heart. "

Fang Fang wrote, "a speck of time falls on every man's head, and is a mountain. " . It's been said over and over again in the past.

This epidemic for me is relatively lucky, because of the family and friends are fortunate to be safe and sound. One of the aunts was probably infected, and Dr. Thawne saw a CT, and 80% of the time, she went home to take her medication, and she didn't have a nucleic acid test scheduled, but she got better.

But it is also certain that there are some people who have been affected or even died, who suffer in silence, do not know how to make a sound, and do not know how to make a sound.

Years ago, an old classmate expressed his anger as a family member in a group of friends. I went to greet her situation, the original diabetic complications in the hospital relatives were "chased" out of the hospital. A few days later I asked him again, the family has passed away unfortunately.

Another is a friend of my mother's. My husband had two kidney operations a few years ago. He went to Xiehe Hospital for dialysis on the 1st and 2nd Day of the 1st Lunar Month. We didn't know if he had a new pneumonia. Byg's car took a full day to pick him up, and he was told to wait 15 days before picking up the ashes.

Aunt did not take the initiative to say, mother heard the news from other friends, also did not dare to ask her directly, just like the usual send during the New Year greetings.

Classmates there are pregnant mothers, just pregnant, the expected date of birth in April or may have to be put on hold. It's a good thing they're not due for another two months.

The disaster itself is a start, but secondary disasters are even more heart-wrenching. Work Stoppage, no income but life to go on, a series of chain reaction will be reflected one after another.

It is not easy in the context of the economic downturn. Production and management have been completely shelved. The layer upon layer of influence on large, medium and small enterprises and private self-employed people is transmitted to everyone. For example, the most important thing for Wuhan people is that it is too early, early-stage stall owners have to pay rent for no income but continue to worry. Some catering industry can also rely on take-out to save themselves, other no way out, can not transform how to do.

Some shop friends, I can only encourage them to say, "go on! The end of the epidemic we will retaliate consumption, we must hold until that day! "

Some media have reported many such individual cases, this is also a topic on Weibo, I have not had the heart to read carefully, too difficult, mortgage loans, car loans, loans, debts... there are small shops for the Spring Festival this peak sales period to stock up on goods, now it's sitting in a warehouse. If the goods can be stored well, can not be kept, expired and spoiled can only be turned into a loss.

During the outbreak, many property developers cut rents for businesses such as Vanda, for example, and seaport city is said to have cut rents by 50% . Prada, which rents $300,000 a day at Times Square, closed after last year's turmoil and the current outbreak.

A friend in Shenzhen got a promise from the landlord to postpone the rent payment, and I tried to ask the landlord in Hong Kong to reduce the rent. I tried to tell the landlord, because most of my clients are mainlanders, and the impact of this outbreak, Hong Kong closed customers can not come over, so my income has been affected. Can I reduce the rent as appropriate?

In the common stereotype, Hong Kong people are some "axis" , or contract spirit of cultivation by the rules. To reduce the rent, I just try to try the mentality, did not expect, the landlord small brother actually replied that we can reduce the rent in March by HK $1,200. I don't know if his family was affected by the outbreak, but everyone's trying to give

My landlord is a very lovely family, the house was originally for the son married to live, decoration accessories are good, and then had a grandson to move.

For the past two years or so, every time the house came across something that needed fixing, they were there to help me fix it and replace the parts.

An old friend of the landlord's grandfather, a sailor, lived above us, and the two of them used to sail together. UPSTAIRS GRANDPA was the ship's electrician, 70-year-old gray hair, in the home with a ladder to help me repair the chandelier, repair the plug, always smiling. He told me that he had seen the building rise from the ground in 1975, with a view of Victoria Harbour from his window... and that he had persuaded a friend to buy it in 2006 for more than $1 million.

When the family's washing machine broke down in December, the landlord promptly bought a new one the next day and arranged for it to be delivered.

Another good friend in Hong Kong also tried to apply for a rent reduction. The landlord initially complained about his difficulty and politely refused. After a few days, he offered a new solution: he could reduce the rent, but it's a one-year contract extension until July next year (lock-in on price and rent) . The impact of the rental housing market has also begun.

People really are the sum total of their experiences.

Many of Hong Kong Drift's friends chose to leave Hong Kong with regret, in large part because of the bad experience they had here, the leaky house, the landlord who checks in every once in a while, the noisy living environment, office politics at work, and so on.

Fortunately, the people I met and experienced were all right. They added to my image of Hong Kong and deepened my sense of belonging to the city.

Now the reverse is also the same, we are Wuhan people, we are Hubei People, we are Hong Kong drift new immigrants.

Despite all the voices of doubt (there are so many voices in the world after all) , the only thing we can do and should do is to be ourselves.

The Sun came shining into the room.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The second blood draw after the camp.

The first needle went in but could not find the vein. The two girls turned the needle for half a day without finding the vein. The other brother replaced his left arm and pumped half a pipe with a syringe. The girl next to me told me to look at her face, not at the needle.

"I grew up with thin blood vessels, which are hard to find, " I said in Broken Cantonese. These days, I answer the phone and talk to the staff, all trying to speak Cantonese, i think the end of the isolation period of Cantonese speaking level can also be a step up the girl encouraged me in the room more wipe the floor (seems to mean?) , probably want me to exercise more.

Back in 2016, when I was hospitalized in Hong Kong, I had to go to a public clinic near my home to get an injection after being discharged from the hospital for seven days. There was a needle in his hand, a rainy day fell (too bad) , left in the back of the hand of the needle is estimated to be crooked, medicine can not play in.

The nurse in the clinic gave me a new indwelling needle, and I couldn't find a vein for half a day. The super-gentle little brother was so anxious that he "almost cried" and kept apologizing to me. It took three or four hand changes to make it work.

In my own experience in Hong Kong, except for the initial difficulty in understanding Cantonese and having some language difficulties, the medical staff were very gentle and impressed.

There are two more blood tests to follow, one on Thursday and one on Monday, and one more on nucleic acid (nasal sampling) .

Some campers have some opinions about the arrangements for blood taking, for fear of affecting health, for personal privacy, or for getting a blue arm after the first blood draw.

Everyone in the group to persuade people concerned to try to cooperate with the test, the virus is uncertain, multiple tests to their more assured, but also to the outside people have a challenge to a confession. What's more, compared to the $3,000-plus we spent in the U.S. , we still get free checkups. (super optimistic)

"When I'm out of quarantine, I have a health certificate. Don't talk to me if you don't have a health certificate! " Laughed one sister. "It's a kind of pride to have a health certificate. "

In the evening, several sisters in the group began to organize a "thanksgiving meeting" , calling everyone to sing and shout slogans through the Windows at 8 o'clock the next night, 30 people soon called together.

Go China, go Wuhan, Go Hong Kong.

What's the proper order for these three?

It was as if the Hong Kong worker had arrived in Wuhan

What language would be appropriate? Would you like to speak Wuhan?

Hong Kong workers arrived at Wuhan Airport Shouting Mandarin as a sign of respect for fitting in, as we do now, and chose Mandarin and Cantonese twice.

The common people know Thanksgiving, thanksgiving is the heart of the spontaneous, do not need to call.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Thanksgiving meeting" after many discussions to finalize the program

March 10,2020, day 6 of Tuesday quarantine

Wuhan added 17 new cases, the number of sharp decline, victory in sight!

Today, I finally feel the temperature rise, you can wear short sleeves in the room.

The wind whistled in and the towels and laundry dried quickly.

The whole country except Wuhan Area Clears Zero One after another, the shelter all rests the cabin.

This time, spring should really come.

The evening gratitude meeting continued to heat up in the group, bringing together more than 50 campers.

To be honest, this is probably the most positive time of my life, thanks to the unity and optimism of my friends.

A camper in Hubei's wechat group said the Foreign Office could not reach a stranded 66-year-old man, who only had a Hong Kong phone and no wechat. Fortunately, he was finally found last night.

During the siege of Wuhan, especially in the first two weeks, the subsequent arrangements under the order of the siege have not kept up, and many times the people are in a state of self-help. The help of the community is kept up bit by bit.

It's hard to imagine not being able to use the Internet and not knowing what to do when you're in a state of quarantine and then you don't have supplies.

A couple of grandparents who live downstairs don't have wechat, and their granddaughter joins our community and often asks my mother or the community staff to pick up the goods and put them in front of his house. GRANDPA hearing is not too good, the group purchase of frozen chicken to help him understand the home, the mother in the door called no one answer, can only send wechat tell granddaughter to call again.

Thank God for the Magic Internet.

The previous article spread out under the retweets of many friends and the Hubei Youth Association. Those who had not joined the wechat group found me through the public account, and then found the "organization. ".

There are also students stranded in Wuhan, missed the final registration deadline is still in Wuhan Home Distance School.

If you are stranded in Hubei and need to return to Hong Kong, but have not joined the group, welcome to leave a message in the background, or add my wechat Qr code at the end of the article, we all share the information of going home.

"I've been in Hong Kong for so many years, I didn't know there were so many of us. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I had to take a video on my phone, and I copied a copy of the lyrics by hand

At 2:30 pm, the speech of the Wechat Group of the Thanksgiving meeting was rehearsed.

Wuhan sister-in-law's spirit is too good. Exciting.

Starting at 7 pm, the group continues to go over the final details

It started at 7:30, and I was a little nervous and excited.

Turn off the room lights and turn on the cell phone flash at 7:55.

Lights on at 8:00, start on time, chant and chant.

Everyone take a video on their cell phone.

Downstairs, there is also a "tomorrow will be better" music sing, holding the flag waiting for us to go home light.

And the one with the baby.

My friends say I'm in a new media camp... cutting movies all the time

Our upstairs campers also have children to participate in the childish voice with a chorus, followed by shouting "come on" , especially touching.

Hard in here with the isolation of children, a small special experience, growing up must be unforgettable precious memories.

Touched.

People who are grateful are also more moved.

While all of this, for unknown and well known reasons, was not allowed to spread widely, groups of friends uploaded videos to various platforms were taken down one after another.

But what I really want to do is simply say thank you.

I would like to thank the Hong Kong government for taking US home, as well as the hard work and dedication of the community.

As Zhang Weili said, this is "a matter for all mankind. " No matter where we are, we are all facing up to it.

Fang Fang's diary, from "Five" and "six" dimensions up to today, has risen to "nine-dimensional space" (the public number of the diary is constantly changing) .

After articles disappeared and were later restricted from being reposted on other public accounts, netizens responded by upgrading to generating images, PDF files, and reposting them in wechat conversations and in wechat friends'circles in a bookmarking way.

The same is true of people's Avon.

We keep asking questions, hoping for a truth that will stop blaming each other, and it needs to be answered.

Engagement on public issues is one of the few benefits of the epidemic.

Everyone has to be dragged into this battle, to fight (in one way or another) , to trace where things went wrong, where things went wrong, and even deeper.

If we remain silent today, or if we are forced to remain silent, who can guarantee that we will survive the next disaster.
